skip to content skip to content #HealthiestWeightFL Return to the Florida Department of Health Home Strategies Activities Resources Partners Every Kid Healthy™ Week April 25-29, 2016 Healthy kids are better learners! Every Kid Healthy™ Week is an annual observance created to celebrate school health and wellness achievements. Observed during the last week of April each year, this special week shines a spotlight on the link between nutrition, physical activity and learning–because healthy kids learn better! Everyone in the country can get involved and be a part of the solution to help support sound nutrition, regular physical activity and health-promoting programs in schools. In 2014, 485 school events were registered in 37 states, with more than 215,000 parent, teacher and student participants. In 2015, more than 1,000 schools nationwide committed to host an Every Kid Healthy Week event. The Florida Department of Health partnered with elementary schools around the state to host Every Kid Healthy Week events. We encourage you to join the action too! Here are examples of what you can do: Hold a healthy taste test Students can taste local produce that is in season Offer whole wheat versions of students’ favorite baked goods Reenergize your school grounds Build a school garden Clean up trash littered on school grounds Plant trees or flowers around school campus Teach fitness classes to the children Local gyms could come teach Zumba or yoga to the students Teachers could use workout DVDs in their classrooms Host a family fitness event at the school Select activities that meet interests of all ages and skill levels Activities could include tug-of-war, sack and relay races, obstacle courses and water balloon toss Invite the community and parents to participate with students in a Walk-A-Thon Visit Action for Healthy Kids to get more ideas or learn how to get started! Healthiest Weight Florida is a public-private collaboration bringing together state agencies, not for profit organizations, businesses, and entire communities to help Florida's children and adults make choices about healthy eating and active living. For Adults For Children Connect with us: 2585 Merchants Row Boulevard Tallahassee, Florida 32399 • 850-245-4444. This page was last modified on: 04/04/2016
